examples.en: My behavior was petty and stupid. I apologize.
How can she be so petty?
He became involved in petty crime as a teenager.
I'm sick of all their petty rules and regulations.
It would be churlish to offer such petty criticism.
They have been in almost every variety of crime, from petty larceny down to downright murder.
A lot of drug addicts get into petty crime to support their habit.
Britain is suffering an epidemic of petty crime.
She refused to respond to their petty slights.
He was a successful basketball coach, but many people regarded him as a petty despot.
Somehow the debate devolved into a petty competition to see who could get more applause.
He is known as a petty, unrelenting wrangler who likes argument for the sake of argument.
I'm tired of your petty little schemes.
I didn't want to get caught up in endless petty arguments.
I know you're not happy, but there's no need to resort to petty sarcasms to make your point.
Over time, her petty thefts aggregated a significant shortfall in the company's books.
